sec.p:
Here we propose the LTR Assembly Index (LAI) for assessing the de novo assembly quality of intergenic and repetitive sequences. The LAI is a standardized metric based on LTR retrotransposons that account for the largest genome component in most plant genomes. The definition of raw LAI is described as follows:
